# Type Conversion Chart

| Conversion | Type | Casting Required? | Example |
|------------|------|------------------|---------|
| byte → short | Widening | ❌ No | `short s = b;` |
| short → int | Widening | ❌ No | `int x = s;` |
| int → long | Widening | ❌ No | `long l = x;` |
| long → float | Widening | ❌ No | `float f = l;` |
| float → double | Widening | ❌ No | `double d = f;` |
| char → int | Widening | ❌ No | `int x = 'A';` |
| double → float | Narrowing | ✅ Yes | `float f = (float)d;` |
| float → long | Narrowing | ✅ Yes | `long l = (long)f;` |
| long → int | Narrowing | ✅ Yes | `int x = (int)l;` |
| int → short | Narrowing | ✅ Yes | `short s = (short)x;` |
| int → byte | Narrowing | ✅ Yes | `byte b = (byte)x;` |
| int → char | Narrowing | ✅ Yes | `char c = (char)x;` |

---

# Widening Order

```text
byte → short → int → long → float → double
                 ↘
                  char
```

---

# Interview Cheat Code

```text
Smaller → Bigger  = Automatic (Widening)

Bigger → Smaller = Casting Required (Narrowing)

Widening = Safe

Narrowing = Possible Data Loss
```

